1. Executive Summary
Oracle's DBSAT readout on March 10, 2026 identified significant security gaps across all five assessment categories for Grainger's Oracle 19c environment. This document is a revised remediation plan constrained to native Oracle 19c Enterprise Edition capabilities only — no additional product licenses (TDE, OKV, Database Vault, Data Masking Pack, AVDF, or Data Safe) are in scope.

Three categories can be substantially or fully remediated at no cost using built-in Oracle features. One finding (data at rest encryption) has NO native fix — it requires the Advanced Security Option (ASO), which is a paid add-on. This residual risk must be formally accepted and documented.

Network encryption (Native Network Encryption) is already implemented and requires no further action.

