3.5 Monitor & Audit Activity — Rating: YELLOW — FULLY FIXABLE
All audit gaps identified by DBSAT are fixable using Oracle 19c Unified Auditing, which is included in the database at no additional cost. Oracle 19c uses Unified Auditing by default.

Step 1: Verify Unified Auditing is Enabled
✓	Confirm Unified Auditing mode:
◦	SELECT value FROM v$option WHERE parameter = 'Unified Auditing';
◦	If TRUE, Unified Auditing is active. If FALSE, the database was linked with traditional auditing — contact Oracle Support to relink.

Step 2: Create All Missing Audit Policies
✓	LOGOFF events:
◦	CREATE AUDIT POLICY audit_logoff ACTIONS LOGOFF;
◦	AUDIT POLICY audit_logoff;

✓	Database management actions (startup/shutdown/alter system):
◦	CREATE AUDIT POLICY audit_db_mgmt
◦	  ACTIONS COMPONENT = DATAPUMP EXPORT,
◦	  ACTIONS ALTER SYSTEM, ALTER DATABASE;
◦	AUDIT POLICY audit_db_mgmt BY USERS WITH GRANTED ROLES DBA;

✓	Password change events:
◦	CREATE AUDIT POLICY audit_pwd_change ACTIONS ALTER USER;
◦	AUDIT POLICY audit_pwd_change;

✓	Protect the audit trail itself (AUDSYS.AUD$UNIFIED):
◦	CREATE AUDIT POLICY audit_trail_protection
◦	  ACTIONS SELECT ON AUDSYS.AUD$UNIFIED,
◦	          DELETE ON AUDSYS.AUD$UNIFIED,
◦	          UPDATE ON AUDSYS.AUD$UNIFIED;
◦	AUDIT POLICY audit_trail_protection;

✓	Synonym management:
◦	CREATE AUDIT POLICY audit_synonyms
◦	  ACTIONS CREATE SYNONYM, DROP SYNONYM, CREATE PUBLIC SYNONYM, DROP PUBLIC SYNONYM;
◦	AUDIT POLICY audit_synonyms;

✓	Data Pump exports (CRITICAL — prevents undetected bulk data exfiltration):
◦	CREATE AUDIT POLICY audit_datapump
◦	  ACTIONS COMPONENT = DATAPUMP EXPORT;
◦	AUDIT POLICY audit_datapump;

✓	Privileged account usage (SYS, SYSTEM, SYSDBA):
◦	AUDIT POLICY ORA_SECURECONFIG;     -- built-in policy, enable it
◦	AUDIT POLICY ORA_DATABASE_PARAMETER;
◦	AUDIT POLICY ORA_ACCOUNT_MGMT;

Step 3: Verify All Policies Are Active
✓	Confirm all policies are enabled:
◦	SELECT policy_name, enabled_option, entity_name, success, failure
◦	FROM audit_unified_enabled_policies ORDER BY policy_name;

Step 4: Audit Log Retention
✓	Set audit trail retention to at minimum 12 months (adjust per compliance requirements):
◦	-- Check current purge job schedule:
◦	SELECT * FROM dba_audit_mgmt_config_params;
◦	
◦	-- Set retention to 12 months (720 days):
◦	BEGIN DBMS_AUDIT_MGMT.SET_AUDIT_TRAIL_PROPERTY(
◦	  DBMS_AUDIT_MGMT.AUDIT_TRAIL_UNIFIED,
◦	  DBMS_AUDIT_MGMT.OS_FILE_RETENTION_PERIOD, 720); END;
◦	/

✓	Without a centralized SIEM (AVDF/Data Safe not available), schedule a weekly DBA review of the unified audit trail for anomalous events:
◦	SELECT event_timestamp, db_username, action_name, object_name, sql_text
◦	FROM unified_audit_trail
◦	WHERE event_timestamp > SYSDATE - 7
◦	  AND action_name IN ('EXPORT','DELETE','LOGOFF','ALTER USER')
◦	ORDER BY event_timestamp DESC;
 
